 Amazon Prime Data Analysis Guide: Tableau & Power BI

 Tableau Implementation

 1. Donut Chart (Movies vs TV Shows Distribution)
- Load Data:
  - Open Tableau and connect to Amazon Prime dataset

- Create Base Chart:
  - Drag Type field to Rows shelf
  - Drag Type to Columns shelf
  - Drag Number of Records to Angle shelf
  - Convert to Pie Chart from Marks dropdown

- Create Donut Effect:
  - Duplicate Number of Records on Rows shelf
  - Change one to Circle in Marks card
  - Reduce circle size for donut hole

- Add Labels:
  - Drag Type to Label shelf
  - Add Number of Records for percentages
  - Set Quick Table Calculation to Percent of Total

- Format:
  - Customize colors with Type on Color shelf
  - Adjust labels to show percentage and type

 2. Area Chart (Releases by Year and Type)
- Base Setup:
  - Drag Release Year to Columns
  - Drag Number of Records to Rows
  - Select Area Chart from Marks

- Add Type Breakdown:
  - Drag Type field to Color shelf

- Format:
  - Add title
  - Adjust colors for Movies vs TV Shows
  - Modify axes and gridlines

 3. Horizontal Bar Chart (Top 10 Genres)
- Create Base Chart:
  - Drag Genre to Rows
  - Drag Number of Records to Columns

- Configure Display:
  - Sort Number of Records descending
  - Filter for Top 10 by Sum(Number of Records)

- Format:
  - Adjust bar appearance
  - Add title
  - Add Genre to Color shelf

 4. Map (Shows by Country)
- Create Base Map:
  - Drag Country to Rows
  - Set geographic role if needed

- Add Metrics:
  - Drag Number of Records to Size shelf
  - Drag Number of Records to Color shelf

- Format:
  - Adjust map layers
  - Add title
  - Configure tooltips

 5. Text Sheet (Movie Descriptions)
- Basic Setup:
  - Drag Title to Rows
  - Drag Description to Text in Marks

- Add Filtering:
  - Add Title to Filters
  - Create Parameter for interactive selection

- Format:
  - Adjust font properties
  - Add title
  - Configure text layout

 6. Interactive Dashboard
- Initial Setup:
  - Create new dashboard
  - Add all worksheets

- Add Interactivity:
  - Configure dashboard actions
  - Set up filters/highlights

- Add Control Elements:
  - Add relevant filters
  - Configure filter application scope

- Format Dashboard:
  - Adjust layout
  - Add title
  - Configure borders and spacing

